 start of the British Invasion.]] The 'British Invasion' was a phenomenon that
 occurred in the mid-1960s when rock and pop music acts from the United
 Kingdom, as well as other aspects of British
 culture, became popular in the US, and then throughout the world. Bands such as
 The Beatles, The Kinks, [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/the-kinks-
 mn0000100160 Allmusic bio The Kinks] The Rolling Stones, and The Who [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/the-who-
 mn0000577627 Allmusic bio The Who] would get their start during this time
 and go on to make a lasting impact on the US music scene. Perone, James E.
 Mods,Rockers, and the Music of the British Invasion. Westport, CT:
 Praeger,2009. Print.
